              <h3>How does salt air affect paint in Gulf Shores?</h3>
              <p>
                Salt air is extremely corrosive and can cause paint to fail quickly through oxidation and 
                adhesion problems. We use marine-grade paints with salt-resistant properties and specialized 
                primers that create a barrier against salt penetration. Regular maintenance and the right 
                paint system are essential for protecting your Gulf Shores property from salt damage.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3>Do you work on beachfront properties?</h3>
              <p>
                Yes, we have extensive experience with Gulf Shores beachfront properties. We understand 
                the unique challenges of elevated beach houses, including access difficulties, wind exposure, 
                and the need for extra-durable paint systems. We also work around turtle nesting seasons 
                and other environmental considerations that affect beachfront properties.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3>What's the best time of year to paint in Gulf Shores?</h3>
              <p>
                Fall and early spring typically offer the best conditions, with lower humidity and fewer 
                storms. We avoid peak hurricane season (August-October) for exterior work when possible. 
                Winter can work for interior projects, but we're careful about temperature and humidity 
                levels. We always check weather forecasts and plan accordingly.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3>Do you work with vacation rental properties?</h3>
              <p>
                Absolutely. We understand the unique needs of vacation rental properties, including 
                quick turnarounds between guests, durable finishes that can withstand heavy use, and 
                flexible scheduling around rental bookings. We work with property management companies 
                and individual owners to minimize disruption to rental income.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3>How do you protect landscaping during exterior painting?</h3>
              <p>
                We take special care with Gulf Shores' often extensive landscaping, including native 
                plants and beach vegetation. We use drop cloths, plastic sheeting, and careful masking 
                to protect plants from paint overspray. We also coordinate with homeowners about any 
                special plants that need extra protection, especially salt-tolerant species that are 
                common in coastal landscapes.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
